Subject: [PATCH] drm/amd/display: Revert dram_clock_change_latency for DCN2.1
References: bsc#1183424
Git-commit: 436baf29fcab13d7603dc81e28ca76cb5ed9a637
Git-repo: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/agd5f/linux
Patch-mainline: Queued in subsystem maintainer repository

[WHY & HOW]
Using values provided by DF for latency may cause hangs in
multi display configurations. Revert change to previous value.

Tested-by: Daniel Wheeler <daniel.wheeler@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Sung Lee <sung.lee@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Haonan Wang <Haonan.Wang2@amd.com>
Acked-by: Eryk Brol <eryk.brol@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/dc/dcn21/dcn21_resource.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/dc/dcn21/dcn21_resource.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/dc/dcn21/dcn21_resource.c
index 8e8ce89b30dc..644a91c95178 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/dc/dcn21/dcn21_resource.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/dc/dcn21/dcn21_resource.c
@@ -296,7 +296,7 @@ struct _vcs_dpi_soc_bounding_box_st dcn2_1_soc = {
 	.num_banks = 8,
 	.num_chans = 4,
 	.vmm_page_size_bytes = 4096,
-	.dram_clock_change_latency_us = 11.72,
+	.dram_clock_change_latency_us = 23.84,
 	.return_bus_width_bytes = 64,
 	.dispclk_dppclk_vco_speed_mhz = 3600,
 	.xfc_bus_transport_time_us = 4,
